1 (7) Where the jurisdiction of a planning unit includes or is adjacent to a military
2 installation, a representative of the military installation may be a nonvoting ex
3 officio member of the commission, in addition to the number of members
4 specified for that planning commission, to advise on matters relating to national
5 security or other concerns for the installation.
6 (8) If one (1) city only joins with one (1) county, then each shall have equal
7 representation.
8 (9)[(8)] Except as provided in KRS 100.137, at least one (1) of the county
9 representatives of the planning commission of a joint planning unit containing a
10 county with an unincorporated area population exceeding one thousand (1,000)
11 persons shall be a resident of the unincorporated area of that county.
12 (10)[(9)] Whenever this chapter requires a city without its consent to belong to a joint
13 planning unit, then KRS 100.137 shall apply.
14 Section 3. KRS 100.137 is amended to read as follows:
15 (1) Except in a consolidated local government, counties with a population of 300,000
16 or more inhabitants shall be a planning unit and shall have a planning commission
17 which commission shall be composed of three (3) members, who are nonresidents
18 of the largest city of the county, appointed by the county judge/executive of such
19 county; three (3) members who are residents of the largest city of the county
20 appointed by the mayor of that city; and the mayor of the largest city, or his or her
21 designee; the county judge/executive, or his or her designee; the director of works
22 of the largest city in the county; and the county road engineer. The county
23 judge/executive and the mayor together shall ensure that three (3) of the six (6)
24 appointees are citizens who have no direct financial interest in the land
25 development and construction industry. If the commission appoints a citizen
26 member to fill a vacancy, the commission shall ensure that the balance is
27 maintained. Where the jurisdiction of a planning unit includes or is adjacent to a
Page 2 of 5
